-- join_subscriptions_companies_plans.sql
```sql
-- Join subscriptions with users and companies, handle missing companies
SELECT
  s.subscription_id,
  s.user_id,
  s.plan_id,
  s.started_at,
  s.ended_at,
  s.status,
  u.name AS user_name,
  u.email,
  u.company_id,
  c.name AS company_name,
  c.industry
FROM subscriptions s
LEFT JOIN users u ON s.user_id = u.user_id
LEFT JOIN companies c ON u.company_id = c.company_id
WHERE s.status = 'active';
```

-- handle_missing_plan_ids.sql
```sql
-- Filter subscriptions to only include those with valid plan_ids
SELECT
  s.subscription_id,
  s.user_id,
  s.plan_id,
  s.started_at,
  s.ended_at,
  s.status,
  u.name AS user_name,
  u.email,
  u.company_id,
  c.name AS company_name,
  c.industry,
  p.tier
FROM subscriptions s
LEFT JOIN users u ON s.user_id = u.user_id
LEFT JOIN companies c ON u.company_id = c.company_id
LEFT JOIN plans p ON s.plan_id = p.plan_id
WHERE s.status = 'active' AND p.plan_id IS NOT NULL;
```

-- calculate_monthly_metrics.sql
```sql
-- Calculate monthly subscription metrics grouped by month, tier, and industry
WITH active_subscriptions AS (
  SELECT
    s.subscription_id,
    s.user_id,
    s.plan_id,
    u.company_id,
    c.industry,
    p.tier,
    s.started_at,
    s.ended_at,
    DATE_TRUNC(s.started_at, MONTH) AS month
  FROM subscriptions s
  LEFT JOIN users u ON s.user_id = u.user_id
  LEFT JOIN companies c ON u.company_id = c.company_id
  LEFT JOIN plans p ON s.plan_id = p.plan_id
  WHERE s.status = 'active' AND p.plan_id IS NOT NULL
  GROUP BY s.subscription_id, s.user_id, s.plan_id, u.company_id, c.industry, p.tier, s.started_at, s.ended_at
),
monthly_counts AS (
  SELECT
    month,
    tier,
    industry,
    COUNT(DISTINCT subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
    COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) AS unique_users
  FROM active_subscriptions
  GROUP BY month, tier, industry
),
monthly_revenue AS (
  SELECT
    event_month AS month,
    tier,
    industry,
    SUM(amount) AS total_mrr
  FROM billing_events
  LEFT JOIN active_subscriptions AS s
    ON s.subscription_id = billing_events.subscription_id
    AND DATE_TRUNC(s.started_at, MONTH) = billing_events.event_month
  WHERE event_type = 'renewal' OR event_type = 'new_subscription'
  GROUP BY month, tier, industry
)
SELECT
  mc.month,
  mc.tier,
  mc.industry,
  mc.active_subscriptions,
  COALESCE(mr.total_mrr, 0) AS total_mrr,
  mc.unique_users
FROM monthly_counts mc
LEFT JOIN monthly_revenue mr ON mc.month = mr.month AND mc.tier = mr.tier AND mc.industry = mr.industry
ORDER BY mc.month, mc.tier, mc.industry;
